1
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:34,990
[OVERDO]

2
00:01:35,259 --> 00:01:37,870
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:50,229 --> 00:01:51,590
Come.

4
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:52,789
Good boy.

5
00:01:57,950 --> 00:01:59,280
Sit. Come.

6
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,680
Sit on my lap.

7
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,590
Good boy.

8
00:02:06,790 --> 00:02:08,430
Help me

9
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:10,000
complete a small task

10
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,030
before you go to sleep, okay?

11
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,520
Come.

12
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:19,710
All the children in the orphanage

13
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,079
will come to this room

14
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:24,240
and eat a piece of candy like this.

15
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,870
Because

16
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:28,520
this is your only way

17
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:30,120
to never

18
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,110
go hungry.

19
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:34,840
Come.

20
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,079
Pick a color.

21
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:52,680
You like the pink one?

22
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:57,240
These different-colored candies

23
00:02:58,630 --> 00:03:01,710
represent different parts of your body.

24
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:02,840
The pink one

25
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:08,360
means you volunteer to give up a leg.

26
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,630
Now, I

27
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:14,190
will let you experience

28
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:17,430
how a broken leg can keep your belly full.

29
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,400
Who is it?

30
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:26,680
Dazhuang?

31
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:34,310
Dazhuang?

32
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:36,800
Dazhuang?

33
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,190
Always pranking.

34
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:51,910
Who are you?

35
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,079
Are you human or a ghost?

36
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:05,400
It's so late.

37
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,130
Why aren't you resting?

38
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:12,000
Y-Y-You...

39
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,590
Y-You are...

40
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:16,510
You are so forgetful, Nanny.

41
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,720
We just met earlier today.

42
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,440
Don't you remember?

43
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:26,410
I remember!

44
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,750
You are Miss Fang.

45
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,270
How could I not remember?

46
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,240
I...

47
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,480
Come.

48
00:04:35,430 --> 00:04:36,600
Come, quickly.

49
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:39,120
You little brat.

50
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:47,550
It really hasn't changed at all—

51
00:04:48,159 --> 00:04:49,270
not a single bit.

52
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:52,750
Quick.

53
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:54,100
Quick.

54
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:55,870
She is an honored guest.

55
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:57,120
An honored guest.

56
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:06,860
He's too dirty.

57
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:11,050
There is a dog hole over there.

58
00:05:14,870 --> 00:05:16,560
I crawled through it back then.

59
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,390
But...

60
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:20,290
you won't need it anymore.

61
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,750
Go back quickly.

62
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,720
Y-Y-You are...

63
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,950
You are...

64
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:48,950
Su...

65
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:49,950
Su...

66
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:51,040
Susu?

67
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,409
Impossible.

68
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,800
Susu is already dead.

69
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:00,630
How could a dead person

70
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:02,480
a-a-appear here?

71
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:04,390
Seeking revenge?

72
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:06,800
An evil spirit is seeking revenge?

73
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,600
Nanny.

74
00:06:11,310 --> 00:06:12,360
My body's warm.

75
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,910
I'm not some evil spirit.

76
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:15,800
It's...

77
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:17,600
It's warm...

78
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,480
Warm...

79
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,800
You're still alive!

80
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:25,920
Thank goodness!

81
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,430
You've become a noble lady!

82
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,680
I am alive,

83
00:06:29,310 --> 00:06:30,950
but do you remember Xiaolan?

84
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:41,000
L...

85
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:41,950
Xiaolan...

86
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,560
Xiaolan?

87
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:46,070
You have killed too many people—

88
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,290
I'm afraid you can't remember.

89
00:06:51,830 --> 00:06:52,750
I...

90
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,120
I can't remember.

91
00:06:57,430 --> 00:06:58,360
An evil spirit is seeking revenge.

92
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,620
I'm not an evil spirit.

93
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,200
But I can still seek revenge.

94
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,270
Help.

95
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,070
Somebody help!

96
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:10,430
Help!

97
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,720
Help!

98
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,310
Somebody!

99
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:15,240
Help!

100
00:07:32,470 --> 00:07:34,750
This orphanage is always so cold.

101
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:37,240
Don't those lingering wails

102
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:40,800
haunt you every night?

103
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,760
Those you've murdered—

104
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,580
I'll avenge them personally.

105
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:51,240
This is your honor.

106
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,870
The orphans' files over the years

107
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:24,040
should be here.

108
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,120
Found it.

109
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,600
Why are you here?

110
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:04,670
She's not dead yet,

111
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:05,910
don't you know?

112
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:22,510
Don't worry,

113
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,780
I'm not here to pester you.

114
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,640
It's simply because

115
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:28,440
you are Qingyu's fiancée.

116
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,150
The things you do are sloppy

117
00:09:30,150 --> 00:09:31,270
and full of flaws.

118
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,320
I don't care,

119
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,480
but Qingyu's reputation

120
00:09:35,870 --> 00:09:37,670
must never be tainted by murder.

121
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,440
The Huo family arranges for police

122
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,600
to patrol here every night.

123
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,080
They could appear at any time.

124
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,340
Did you plan what to do?

125
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,960
Do you think I'd be unprepared?

126
00:09:51,830 --> 00:09:57,400
[Renxin Orphanage]

127
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:54,200
Deal with this quickly.

128
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,060
Oh my goodness!

129
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,330
Where are the adults in charge?

130
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,200
They went to the new building.

131
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,390
The new orphanage is under renovation.

132
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:19,450
They are all there.

133
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:20,320
It's raining so hard.

134
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,630
What are you doing here

135
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:23,150
instead of sleeping upstairs?

136
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:24,120
Practicing singing.

137
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,670
Nanny Sun said
we didn't sing well enough during the day,

138
00:10:26,670 --> 00:10:28,150
and the nobles didn't like it,

139
00:10:28,150 --> 00:10:29,750
so she told us to practice more.

140
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:30,320
Mister,

141
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,650
could you have a listen?

142
00:10:31,910 --> 00:10:32,750
No, no.

143
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,240
I'm just patrolling around.

144
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:34,840
I'm leaving now.

145
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:35,550
Mister,

146
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:38,240
do you also think we don't sing well,

147
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:40,480
and are unlikable?

148
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,030
That's not it.

149
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:45,240
Then let us sing for you, Uncle.

150
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,840
We learned Polish especially for this.

151
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:49,390
Nanny Sun said
the nobles would surely like it.

152
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:50,030
Start.

153
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:19,440
I didn't expect these children
to be so clever.

154
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,780
They just come from a sad background,

155
00:11:21,790 --> 00:11:23,150
but they are smart.

156
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,510
Well sung!

157
00:11:25,670 --> 00:11:26,910
We need to speed up.

158
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:33,270
All right.

159
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:35,120
That's it for today's singing.

160
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,050
Everyone go upstairs to sleep.

161
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:38,600
Hurry up.

162
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,510
Go to sleep.

163
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,150
Singing out here so late.

164
00:11:48,870 --> 00:11:50,670
You all live on the second floor?

165
00:11:52,630 --> 00:11:53,760
Go to sleep quickly.

166
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:04,790
Who is it?

167
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:07,600
Who's there?

168
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:10,080
Who?

169
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,630
I-Is...

170
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:15,720
Is anyone there?

171
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,030
Anyone here?

172
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:34,130
The matter is settled.

173
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:36,630
I have no intention to celebrate

174
00:13:36,630 --> 00:13:37,840
this murder with you.

175
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,840
You don't need to follow me anymore.

176
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,120
Ren Susu.

177
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,440
What else do you want to do

178
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:53,640
with the name of my brother's fiancée?

179
00:13:54,870 --> 00:13:55,960
Both our hands

180
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:59,130
are tainted from what happened tonight.

181
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:00,750
I suppose there is no need
for either of us

182
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:03,350
to leak this,
bringing trouble upon ourselves

183
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:05,480
and destroy each other again,

184
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,480
right?

185
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,440
Ren Susu,

186
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,600
what right do you have to lecture me?

187
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,460
Just now at the orphanage,

188
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:23,960
if that nanny crawled out
to call for help,

189
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,360
what would you do
if you were trapped there?

190
00:14:47,270 --> 00:14:49,840
The corridor outside the room
is 36 meters long.

191
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:50,790
At the stairwell,

192
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:52,250
there is an iron threshold

193
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,270
25 centimeters high.

194
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:56,790
In her state
of hypothermia and blood loss,

195
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:59,160
Nanny Sun couldn't possibly crawl out.

196
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,880
I left her with one breath

197
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,320
to let her experience fear.

198
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:06,790
Yet you gave her a quick death.

199
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,200
Taking a step back,

200
00:15:12,790 --> 00:15:14,390
I'm your brother's fiancée.

201
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,030
No matter what I do,

202
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:19,080
only your brother
has the right to question it.

203
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,150
You don't have the right.

204
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,500
Whether I have the right or not

205
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,050
is not for you to decide.

206
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,030
Xiaolan,

207
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:04,390
♪ Fantasies reduced to ash ♪

208
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,390
I finally did it.

209
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:06,410
♪ In a raging fire ♪

210
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,730
This is just the beginning.

211
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:09,200
Rest assured,

212
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,120
together with the wronged souls
of the dead children,

213
00:16:10,540 --> 00:16:12,210
♪ Those caught in the wake ♪

214
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:14,180
♪ Now tell only gray lies ♪

215
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,270
I will take revenge

216
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:17,450
on those who did evil back then.

217
00:16:18,230 --> 00:16:19,380
♪ Willingly ♪

218
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:21,390
♪ Surrendering the naive visage ♪

219
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,510
♪ Of the past ♪

220
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,320
Those animals

221
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:26,700
-chose us like goods.
-Come here. Hurry.

222
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:28,720
-If it weren't for you...
-Go!

223
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,600
Protecting me and Xiaoqing all along,

224
00:16:28,870 --> 00:16:30,620
♪ With no expectation of dawn ♪

225
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:34,610
we might have died a long time ago.

226
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:36,080
Go! Go!

227
00:16:36,150 --> 00:16:36,840
Hurry up!

228
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:37,630
Hurry up!

229
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:40,140
♪ Wandering beneath a pitch-black sky ♪

230
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:38,910
Go!

231
00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:42,280
♪ I smell no sorrow ♪

232
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,390
Xiaolan!

233
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,240
Stop!

234
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:50,180
[13 years ago, Nancheng]

235
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,820
♪ Let the story start over ♪

236
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,580
Susu, push this aside!

237
00:16:47,890 --> 00:16:49,990
♪ With a new beginning ♪

238
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,080
Susu!

239
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:55,750
♪ When our paths cross again ♪

240
00:16:55,860 --> 00:16:57,650
♪ I shift my gaze away ♪

241
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,270
Susu.

242
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:01,200
Xiaolan.

243
00:17:00,410 --> 00:17:01,790
♪ Only then can I ♪

244
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,200
Drink some water.

245
00:17:04,450 --> 00:17:06,089
♪ Rid all hope ♪

246
00:17:04,829 --> 00:17:06,359
Drink slowly. Don't choke.

247
00:17:07,589 --> 00:17:08,880
Susu, eat some of this.

248
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,640
I'll figure something out.

249
00:17:09,619 --> 00:17:11,660
♪ No longer able to break free ♪

250
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:12,200
Don't eat it all at once.

251
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:16,119
♪ From the shackles of destiny ♪

252
00:17:17,510 --> 00:17:18,310
Just like this,

253
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,589
♪ No more questioning ♪

254
00:17:19,030 --> 00:17:20,750
we grew up in that hell,

255
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:23,190
♪ The cruel jests of fate ♪

256
00:17:24,069 --> 00:17:26,000
until the Huo family found us.

257
00:17:25,619 --> 00:17:27,270
♪ Now I know to appreciate ♪

258
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:30,990
♪ The calm as it shatters ♪

259
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:33,350
-Nanny Sun.
-Nanny Sun.

260
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:35,400
♪ No longer craving ♪

261
00:17:35,490 --> 00:17:39,430
♪ Absolution from the heavens ♪

262
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:39,830
Baby,

263
00:17:40,980 --> 00:17:43,440
♪ I've walked alone ♪

264
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:43,270
so you're lying here.

265
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:47,350
♪ Into the deserted wilderness ♪

266
00:17:45,550 --> 00:17:47,640
-Playing dead, huh?
-Nanny.

267
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,400
♪ Hunting slowly ♪

268
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:51,160
She's sick.

269
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,030
I'm telling you,

270
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:55,220
♪ Waiting for someone
to sink deep into it ♪

271
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,000
as long as she's not dead,

272
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,640
she has to come with me!

273
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:56,880
Get up!

274
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:58,110
She's sick.

275
00:17:57,460 --> 00:17:59,440
♪ In the chaotic rainy night ♪

276
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,160
Nanny, she's really sick.

277
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:00,790
-The Huo family taking a liking to you...
-She's really sick.

278
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,830
♪ If we brush past each other again ♪

279
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,400
-Is your blessing.
-Nanny, she's sick.

280
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,640
Get up right now!

281
00:18:03,830 --> 00:18:05,510
She's really sick!

282
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:07,110
♪ And have only hatred ♪

283
00:18:05,510 --> 00:18:07,400
-Nanny!
-Nanny!

284
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:11,560
♪ There's no difference ♪

285
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:08,830
She's really sick.

286
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:10,310
She's really sick, Nanny.

287
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,550
If she's sick...

288
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:15,380
♪ No innocent yesterdays ♪

289
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,900
who'll go make the money then?

290
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:16,440
I'll go, Nanny.

291
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,200
I know how to dance.

292
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:19,210
♪ All trapped in the mud ♪

293
